# Trigger Rules Problem

Branching introduces skipped tasks.

This affects downstream execution.

---

# Example Problem

```text id="jlwm80"
Branch A → success
Branch B → skipped
```

Final task may not run automatically.

---

# Trigger Rules

Used to control downstream behavior.

Example:

```python id="jlwm81"
trigger_rule="none_failed_min_one_success"
```

---

# Common Trigger Rules

| Trigger Rule | Meaning              |
| ------------ | -------------------- |
| all_success  | all upstream success |
| one_success  | one upstream success |
| none_failed  | no failures          |

---

# EmptyOperator in Branching

